article.headline: Colgate 83, Texas St. 77
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Kyle Roemer had 24 points and six rebounds to lead Colgate to an 83-77 victory over Texas State in the opening round of the 100 Club Classic on Friday night. The Raiders (3-0) will meet Kennesaw State, which beat Jacksonville State 80-74. in the championship game Saturday night. Roemer is averaging 18.3 points per game. The Raiders got solid play from Tim Pounds, who had a career-high 19 points, and Kendall Chones 11 points and five rebounds. Brandon Bush led the Bobcats (2-1) with 20 points and 10 rebounds. Brent Benson added 12 and Corey Jefferson 11 for Texas State. Roemer had five 3-pointers for Colgate, giving the junior 117 in his career.
